Boil a half-full #kettle{}. Pour the hot water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add @Basmati Rice{150%g} and boil for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain, pop back in the pan and cover.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @British Beef Mince{240%g}, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Break up the mince as it cooks, then drain the fat. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. 

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Next, add the @Curry Powder Mix{1%sachet}, @Rogan Josh Curry Paste{50%g} and @Tomato Puree{30%g} to the mince.

Stir in the @Chickpeas{1%carton} and liquid from the carton, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g}, @Water for the Sauce{50%ml} and @Honey{1%tbsp}.

Bring to a bubble. Simmer, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the @Baby Spinach{40%g} in handfuls so it's piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in the @Butter{20%g}.

Taste and season the curry with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Remove from the heat.

Share the rice and curry between your #bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the @Toasted Flaked Almonds{15%g}.

Enjoy!